{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"116c73b4-d047-4ac6-8405-78942ab493dd","content":"There's no pipeline file in the repo, so here's the general guidance:\n\n### Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script)\n\n**Before (VSTest):**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform):**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: Test\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **Test runner** – `dotnet test` invokes Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly (no `vstest.console`).\n2. **TRX reports** – pass `--logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"`.\n3. **Code coverage** – pass `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` (uses the built-in Microsoft collector).\n4. **Publish results** – add a separate step:\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n> If you use the **Coverlet** collector instead, swap to `--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"` and the output is already Cobertura XML.\n\n### Project-side prerequisite\n\nEnsure each test project references the new platform adapter:\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.7+\" />\n```\n\nMSTest ≥ 3.7 ships with Microsoft.Testing.Platform built in—no extra test-adapter package is needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e47ef9bb-3f9b-4572-912a-46cbf393f198","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the repository. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":620,"requestId":"7038:83273:E1BCC9C:F7E67C5:69F2A815"},"id":"a18e3583-6cdd-4571-98b8-c9266fffde71","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:53:53.212Z","parentId":"635b079d-3ddf-4209-96c6-23ef6e33fcae"}
